            procedure = "Prepare sterile Soybean Casein Digest Medium (Tryptone Soya Broth) in a bulk compounding vessel.;Inject the nutrient media into sterilizing filters and run line filling operations under routine production speeds.;Fill a target minimum of 5,000 up to 10,000 units (vials/syringes) per simulation run. Integrate worst-case interventions (e.g. door open, line stops).;Collect all filled units, physically verify seal integrity, and transfer to microlab incubator racks.;Incubate all units at 20-25°C for 7 days, followed by 30-35°C for 7 days. Inspect units daily for turbidity or growth.;If any contaminated unit is observed, register a critical deviation, initiate CFT investigation, and stop routine production on the line.;A media fill run passes if zero contaminated units are detected out of 5,000+ filled units.",
