            title = "SOP for Biological Indicators (BI) Verification",
            department = "Microlab",
            section = "Validation",
            objective = "To establish the procedure for utilizing biological indicators to verify autoclave sterilization cycles.",
            scope = "All laboratory and manufacturing autoclave qualification runs.",
            responsibility = "Microbiology Analysts perform verification. Validation team documents results.",
            procedure = "Retrieve qualified self-contained biological indicator ampoules containing Geobacillus stearothermophilus spores (min concentration 1.0 x 10^6 spores).;Place BI ampoules at worst-case cold spots inside the autoclave chamber (e.g., near the drain, center of load, bottom rack) alongside load items.;Run the standard sterilization cycle (121°C for 15 minutes, pressure 15 psi).;Once the autoclave cycle completes and cools, retrieve the BI ampoules from the load wearing thermal protection gloves.;Crush the plastic ampoule casing to mix the spores with the nutrient broth and indicator dye inside the tube.;Place the autoclaved BIs and one un-autoclaved control BI inside the incubator at 55-60°C for 48 hours.;Observe color daily: un-autoclaved control must turn yellow (indicates growth). Autoclaved BIs must remain purple/green (indicates sterilization success).",
