            procedure = "Verify that the FBD unit carries a green 'CLEANED' status tag and the line clearance certificate is signed in the batch record.;Check that the finger bag filter is physically intact, clean, and properly shaken. Insert the finger bag securely.;Transfer wet granules container into the FBD product bowl. Clamp the bowl tightly to avoid hot air leakages during runs.;Set the inlet air temperature, exhaust temperature limits, and blower fan speed in the PLC controller as per the batch record (BMR).;Initiate the dryer. Monitor inlet temperature (e.g. 60°C ± 2°C) and shake the filter bag manually or automatically every 15 minutes.;Perform periodic sampling through the sampling port to test Loss on Drying (LOD). Dry until LOD is below the specified monograph limit (e.g. < 2.0% w/w).;Once dry, turn off heating, let the system cool down to ambient temperature, and discharge dry granules into clean, double-lined bins.",
